    {
      "id": "ebf934f9_3b016ee8",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/inventory/sync/lcm/LcmEventsCmHandleStateHandlerAsyncHelper.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 39,
      "message": "seeing those names side-by-side makes clear it is not obvious who does what?!\nie what is the difference between 'producing' something and 'creating' something ?!\ncan we define better names or may just combine the 2 classes into one?!\n\n\ni think the problem term is really 'producing' I know they always use it with events but I think it is misleading. Sender or Publisher is more intuitive. But is that leads to other conflicts or breaks naming conventions maybe we should combine these 2 classes as I mentioned before",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2025-03-26 13:24:32.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "86a59875_f43271c7",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/inventory/sync/lcm/LcmEventsCmHandleStateHandlerAsyncHelper.java",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 39,
      "message": "as discussed, we agreed on the following\nNouns/Classes: Producer (& Consumer)\nVerbs/Methods: send (& receive)\n\nie. the terms Publisher/publish should no longer be used",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2025-03-26 14:15:00.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "ebf934f9_3b016ee8",
      "unresolved": true
    },
